summary: I am a highly ambitious consultant with a PhD in industrial microbiology. I enjoy solving problems related to society and sustainability and thrive on presenting my results clearly and with candour. When working in a team, my ability to recognise and enhance my team-members' talents, and dedication to always support each other, sustain motivation and enthusiasm.

LIFE', 'description': 'From september 2014 untill september 2015 Study Association LIFE celebrated its 3th lustrum. The Lustrumcommitte is responsible for the organization of a variety of educational and social activities to celebrate the lustrum. The committe started in september 2013 to prepare the lustrum year. During this year I was a member of the board of Study Association LIFE, where one of my tasks was to guide this committee through this year. In the year of the lustrum I was discharged from the board and took place in the lustrumcommittee as Commisioner Design. 
during the lustrumyear a variety of social activities were organized by the committee, where my main task was design of all promotionmaterial.
Next to the social activities the committee also organized a minisymposium about the developments of biotechnology in the last few decades. In the preparation of this symposium I was also resonsilbe for the speakers attending this day, next to the promotion material.', 'title': 'Commisioner Design of the Lustrumcommittee', 'employment_type': None}, {'location': None, 'date': {'start': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2013}, 'end': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2014}}, 'company': 'S.V. LIFE', 'description': 'Study Association LIFE organizes social and educational activitites for students of Life Science and Technology. The Study Association is runned by five new students every year. As Secretary I noted every meeting with the board itself, with the educational director and advisor and the general meeting of members. Also the Secretary is responsible for the databases and in- and outcoming mail. 
Next to the responsibilities as Secretary, I designed the new version of the magazine "The Vision of LIFE" and was responsible for its content during this year. This magazine is produces by the Study Association for all its members and colleagues from Leiden University and Delft University of Technology. The magazine contains information about the study association, previous activities and upcoming activities. Also it contains reports about the educational activities organized by the association, stories of member with special extracurricular activities, stories of old-member and their road to their current job and interviews with interesting people within the biotechnology. 

Also each member of the board has to guide some committees, The committees I guided during my year in the board are listed below:
- Lustrumcommittee - responsible of the preparations of the lustrumyear
